args: It appears all are now present.
That's rich, comin' from the one who\njust decided to show up.
I should be thanked for not rebuking\nthose who recklessly ignore orders.
Orders? Idiocy. We have not the type\nof relationship in which commands are\neither given or received.
Yeah, we're free! Isn't that right, Oto?
That's right, Aya. Just because we agree\nwith the things HE says doesn't mean\nwe've become his minions.
Of course. That's how we've always been.\nIf each of us accomplishes what must\nbe done, there will be no interference.
What's there to say? They're puppets\nwho know nothing of freedom.
That's right! Puppets with no idea\nif they even have free will or not!
The little puppets playing in their little\ndelusions... It's almost adorable!
They are weak. Nothing more.\nAnd weakness must be culled.
Yeah, they're a pathetic bunch, all right.
It would appear we are in agreement:\nthey possess strength enough that we\nought to be wary of them.
None here can ever find agreement,\nyet now you all steadfastly hold to the\nsame belief. I find this most abnormal.
I suspect something has occurred to give\nyou pause—perhaps a battle with a foe\nwho proved to be your equals?
You have the right of it: They are strong.\nIt is hopeless to pretend otherwise.
And they're blessed with talent, fortune,\nand friendships...which I find irremissible!
It merely means that the six of us—having\nattained the height of power—now have\nfoes actually worth the slaughter.
Yeah, it's all the same in the end.\nWe'll just go and rip 'em up.
Good. I see it was wise to trust you to act\non your own. Your vigilance will not go to\nwaste in the battle to come.
But from this point forward, I cannot\nhave you simply doing as you please.\nBear that in mind.
Do you still not get it? Not one of us is\nabove or below the other; we neither\ngive nor obey the others' orders.
We won't let anyone interfere with our\nfreedom—not even HIM.
We have no common ideology.\nWe have no single connection.
Pathless. Licentious. Free. Aberrant.\nWe are a group that is not a group,\nwhich is why we are gathered.
But we all seek the same thing.\nI trust I am not mistaken in this?
So WE will reject the world!
And we are all in agreement as to what is\nneeded for that goal.
The treasure of treasures—one with\nthe power to unwind fate itself.
We shall rebel, shatter destiny itself, and\neliminate this world. And to accomplish\nthis, we must have the Dawnshard.
So you have come as well, Nedrick.

I'm not looking to serve as your leader,
but we are all here to use each other as
tools. I will have you live up to the power
I bestowed upon you.
I shall permit no turning away. You need\nnot obey me, nor bend the knee—but I'll\nnot see you veer from our objective.
Move ever towards it, without erring.\nThis is what I gathered you for.
Your concerns are unnecessary; our souls\nwere loosed from this world long ago.
We'll turn away from nothing!\nRight, Oto?
That's right, Aya. Our sights are set\nFIRMLY on our world.
Very well. Then let us be off, so we might\nunmake this world with our own hands.
And we will awaken the world.
